  "text": "Virological suppression was defined as at least 1 plasma VL measurement , 50 copies per milliliter. Virological breakthrough was defined as a single plasma VL . 1000 copies per milliliter having previously achieved virological suppression. Two or more consecutive VL measurements . 1000 copies per milliliter at least 4 weeks apart were defined as virological failure. Patients with a VL . 1000 copies per milliliter were reviewed and received a targeted adherence intervention including counselor home visits, as previously described. [CITATION_1] Although a previous study reported similar proportions of patients with VL measurements .400 and .1000 copies per milliliter during ART, [CITATION_2] the threshold of 1000 copies per milliliter was chosen as it is less likely to reflect random variation and more likely to reflect significant viral breakthrough.",
